 plan that called for standards of learning, statewide high-stakes tests, standards of accreditation, and annual school performance report cards. This book examines factors such as the fate of students who fail state tests, achievement differences between black and white students, ethical issues surrounding accountability measures, and the increasing politicization of local schooling. Educational Leadership in an Age of Accountability shows that accountability pressure has done more than previous reforms to foster instructional leadership.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEducational accountabilityzVirginia. 0aEducational leadershipzVirginia. 0aSchool improvement programszVirginia. 0aTeachingzVirginia. 4aEducation : Educational Administration. 7aEDUCATION / Leadership.2bisacsh1 aButin, Dan W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCurry-Corcoran, Daniel E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuke, Daniel L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuke, Daniel L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGrogan, Margaret, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrogan, Margaret, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHeinecke, Walter F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeinecke, Walter F., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMoon, Tonya R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReck, Brianne L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoland, Pamela B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSherman, Whitney H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSofka, Amy, econtr